cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper deals with sparsification methods for social networks and their impact on various network properties. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the preservation of network structure, which suggests the category cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper uses various algorithms and techniques for sparsification, which could fall under the categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper evaluates the sparsification methods on various network properties, including community structure, which could also place it under the category cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
